  "AGENTS.md": "# snapshot-test Knowledge Map

## About This Project

snapshot-test -- A Python project managed with Harness Engineering practices.

## Language & Tooling

- **Language:** Python (>=3.10)
- **Linter/Formatter:** Ruff
- **Test runner:** pytest
- **Package manager:** pip

## Directory Structure

- \`src/\` -- Application source code
- \`tests/\` -- Test files (pytest)
- \`pyproject.toml\` -- Project metadata and dependencies

## Conventions

- Follow PEP 8 style (enforced by Ruff)
- Use type hints for function signatures
- Tests live in \`tests/\` and mirror \`src/\` structure
- Import sorting managed by Ruff (isort rules)

## Harness Skills

- Use \`harness-brainstorming\` for design exploration
- Use \`harness-planning\` to break features into atomic tasks
- Use \`harness-execution\` to implement tasks with TDD
- Refer to \`harness.config.json\` for project tooling configuration
",
  "harness.config.json": "{
  "version": 1,
  "name": "snapshot-test",
  "agentsMapPath": "./AGENTS.md",
  "docsDir": "./docs",
  "template": {
    "language": "python",
    "version": 1
  },
  "tooling": {
    "packageManager": "pip",
    "linter": "ruff",
    "formatter": "ruff",
    "testRunner": "pytest"
  }
}",
  "pyproject.toml": "[project]
name = "snapshot-test"
version = "0.1.0"
description = ""
requires-python = ">=3.10"
dependencies = []

[project.optional-dependencies]
dev = [
  "pytest>=7.0",
  "ruff>=0.4.0",
]

[tool.ruff]
line-length = 88

[tool.pytest.ini_options]
testpaths = ["tests"]
",
  "ruff.toml": "line-length = 88
target-version = "py310"

[lint]
select = ["E", "F", "I", "N", "W", "UP"]
",
  "src/__init__.py": "",
}
`;

